questions.explanation:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The given statement:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;The National Skill Development Committee conducted an assessment among their trainers and found the performance below mandatory level.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Conclusions:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I: The committee should immediately organise remedial courses and training to improve standards.&amp;nbsp;&amp;rarr; This will help the trainers to get updated with new and fresh ideas.&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Thus, this conclusion does&amp;nbsp;follow.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;II: The committee should terminate poor performers and hire new trainers.&amp;nbsp;&amp;rarr; This is a desperate remedy and it can&amp;#39;t be concluded from the statement that this is an immediate situation.&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Thus, this conclusion does not follow.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Hence, &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;only conclusion I&amp;nbsp;follows&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Given:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The number should be multiplied =&amp;nbsp;&lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(\frac{7}{8}\)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But the number is multiplied by&amp;nbsp;&lt;span class=&quot;math-tex&quot;&gt;\(\frac{17}{8}\)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

