questions.explanation:
&lt;p&gt;Given statement:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Statement: The opposition party criticized the government over the increased unemployment rate.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Conclusions:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I. The statement only mentions that the opposition party criticized the government over the increased unemployment rate. It does not specify that &amp;quot;only&amp;quot; the government is responsible. Hence, the conclusion I does not logically follow beyond a reasonable doubt from the information given.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;II. The statement only mentions the criticism by the opposition party. It does not provide information about whether the government has made any decisions or not. Hence, conclusion II does not logically follow beyond a reasonable doubt from the information given.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So, &lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;Neither I nor II is implicit.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Hence, the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Option (4)&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

