questions.explanation:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The given statement:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;A police officer receives a complaint that an MP of his district is taking bribes in order to facilitate some work.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Conclusions:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I. The police officer should try to investigate the matter and catch the MP red-handed&amp;nbsp;&amp;rarr; This is the job of the police officer to take necessary action when such complaints are made. Thus, the police officer should investigate to know the truth of the matter. Hence, this conclusion follows.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;II. The police officer should wait for some more complaints and then catch the MP-red-handed&amp;nbsp;&amp;rarr; This is not the right thing to do as the police are supposed to protect the interest of the people. Waiting for more complaints would only make some more people suffer. Thus, the action should be immediate on the complaint. Hence, this conclusion does not follow.&lt;/p&gt;

