&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Statement: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There is a general protest from the inhabitants of a certain area that the report submitted on riots in that area has been fabricated based on prejudices and the commission has not presented the whole event.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Conclusions: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I. Another inquiry commission should be sent for proper investigation.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;II. The members of the commission should be severely punished.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Ill. The next commission should consist of inhabitants of that area only.&lt;/p&gt;

questions.explanation:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;Given&lt;/u&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Statement:&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;There is a general protest from the inhabitants of a certain area that the report submitted on riots in that area has been fabricated based on prejudices and the commission has not presented the whole event.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Conclusions:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I. &lt;u&gt;Another inquiry commission should be sent for proper investigation&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In the given statement, it is mentioned that there is a general protest from the inhabitants that the report submitted on riots in that area has been fabricated on prejudices and the commission has not presented the whole event. As it is clear that there is a sense of doubt among the inhabitants regarding the report submitted by the commission which is leading to a protest, therefore, it is safe to conclude that another inquiry commission should be formed for proper investigation.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Therefore, the &lt;strong&gt;conclusion I follows&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;II. &lt;u&gt;The members of the commission should be severely punished&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As in the given statement, it is mentioned that inhabitants believe that the report was fabricated&amp;nbsp;based on prejudices and the commission has not presented the whole event, the members of the commission should be punished for their incomplete&amp;nbsp;and unreasonable report on riots.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Therefore, the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;conclusion II follows&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Ill. &lt;u&gt;The next commission should consist of inhabitants of that area only&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The commission consisting of only inhabitants can lead to a biased report on the riots. The next commission should consist of both inhabitants and other seniors members who can provide an unbiased report.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Therefore,&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;conclusion III not&amp;nbsp;follows&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Hence, the correct answer is &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;Both conclusion&amp;nbsp;I and II follow&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot;.&lt;/p&gt;

