questions.statement:
&lt;p&gt;Read the given paragraph carefully and answer the following question.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Soil erosion is a naturally occurring process that affects all land forms. It refers to the wearing away of a field&amp;#39;s topsoil by natural physical forces of water and wind. Topsoil, which is high in organic matter, fertility and soil life, majorly contributes to the growth of crops. Soil erosion reduces cropland productivity and causes the pollution of watercourses, weltlands and lakes.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Which of the following options does NOT show steps taken to prevent soil erosion?&lt;/p&gt;

questions.explanation:
&lt;p&gt;Protective measures to prevent soil erosion:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1)&amp;nbsp;Use of proper drainage canals&amp;nbsp;&amp;rarr; Man-made canals are made up of concrete and it directs the water in such a way that it prevents the water from going to the fertile land which prevents the wear and tear of the upper layer of the soil.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2)&amp;nbsp;Use&amp;nbsp;of contour plowing&amp;nbsp;&amp;rarr;&amp;nbsp; A farming practice of plowing or planting across of slope following its elevation contour lines. This prevents soil erosion as it does not let water easily flow through the slopes.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;3)&amp;nbsp;Soil erosion is a result of mankind&amp;#39;s unwise actions such as overgrazing or unsuitable cultivating practices&amp;nbsp;&amp;rarr;&amp;nbsp; &lt;strong&gt;It is one of the reasons for soil erosion and not a preventive measure.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;4)&amp;nbsp;Planting provides a protective cover on land, and this allows most of the rainwater to soak into the ground&amp;nbsp;&amp;rarr; Trees hold the soil around it so that it does not get flown easily with rainwater. This is the reason why landslides take place where deforestation is abundant. Thus, planting trees prevents soil erosion.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Hence, &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;option (3)&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; is the correct option.&lt;/p&gt;

